{"parse":{"title":"Liu Xiaofeng (academic)","pageid":38240084,"revid":831192208,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Liu Xiaofeng</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Simplified_Chinese_characters\" title=\"Simplified Chinese characters\">Chinese</a>&#58; <span lang=\"zh-Hans\">\u5218\u5c0f\u67ab</span>, b. 1956) is a contemporary Chinese scholar and a professor at <a href=\"/wiki/Renmin_University_of_China\" title=\"Renmin University of China\">Renmin University of China</a>.  He has been considered the prototypical example of what is called a <a href=\"/wiki/Cultural_Christian\" title=\"Cultural Christian\">cultural Christian</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Simplified_Chinese_characters\" title=\"Simplified Chinese characters\">Chinese</a>&#58; <span lang=\"zh-Hans\">\u6587\u5316\u57fa\u7763\u5f92</span>; <a href=\"/wiki/Pinyin\" title=\"Pinyin\">pinyin</a>&#58; <i><span lang=\"zh-Latn-pinyin\">w\u00e9nhu\u00e0 j\u012bd\u016bt\u00fa</span></i>), meaning a believer who may lack a specific church identification or affiliation, and was, along with <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=He_Guanghu&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"He Guanghu (page does not exist)\">He Guanghu</a>, one of the main forerunners of the academic field of <a href=\"/wiki/Sino-Christian_Theology\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sino-Christian Theology\">Sino-Christian Theology</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Simplified_Chinese_characters\" title=\"Simplified Chinese characters\">simplified Chinese</a>&#58; <span lang=\"zh-Hans\">\u6c49\u8bed\u795e\u5b66</span>; <a href=\"/wiki/Traditional_Chinese_characters\" title=\"Traditional Chinese characters\">traditional Chinese</a>&#58; <span lang=\"zh-Hant\">\u6f22\u8a9e\u795e\u5b78</span>; <a href=\"/wiki/Pinyin\" title=\"Pinyin\">pinyin</a>&#58; <i><span lang=\"zh-Latn-pinyin\">h\u00e0ny\u01d4 sh\u00e9nxu\u00e9</span></i>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  However, in recent years, his interest has shifted from studies in <a href=\"/wiki/Christian_theology\" title=\"Christian theology\">Christian theology</a> to the political theories of <a href=\"/wiki/Leo_Strauss\" title=\"Leo Strauss\">Leo Strauss</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Biography\">Biography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Liu_Xiaofeng_(academic)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Biography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Liu Xiaofeng was born in <a href=\"/wiki/Chongqing\" title=\"Chongqing\">Chongqing</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/China\" title=\"China\">China</a>, in April 1956.\n</p><p>He completed his Bachelor of Arts degree in German language and literature at <a href=\"/wiki/Sichuan_International_Studies_University\" title=\"Sichuan International Studies University\">Sichuan International Studies University</a> before beginning his <a href=\"/wiki/Master_of_Arts\" title=\"Master of Arts\">Master of Arts</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Aesthetics\" title=\"Aesthetics\">aesthetics</a> at <a href=\"/wiki/Peking_University\" title=\"Peking University\">Peking University</a> in 1982, completing it in 1985. He later received a scholarship to study at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Basel\" title=\"University of Basel\">University of Basel</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Switzerland\" title=\"Switzerland\">Switzerland</a> in April 1989, where he completed his <a href=\"/wiki/Ph.D\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ph.D\">Ph.D</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Christian_theology\" title=\"Christian theology\">Christian theology</a> in 1993 on a theological investigation into <a href=\"/wiki/Max_Scheler\" title=\"Max Scheler\">Max Scheler's</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Phenomenology_(philosophy)\" title=\"Phenomenology (philosophy)\">phenomenology</a> and critique of modernity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  He also undertook an extensive translation effort of historical and contemporary Christian texts.  A modern writer commented, \"Liu's writings have had a major impact in China not only on those Chinese who think of themselves as Christian, but on those who are interested in broad analysis of China in the context of the world's current cultural and philosophical era.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> However, his interpretation of Strauss and other modern Western thinkers has been criticized as one-sided and even deeply flawed; his defense of the Chinese Communist Party, and Mao Zedong in particular, does not go well together with Christianity, nor with Classical Western civilization as described by Strauss and his disciples <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>He is a faculty member of Renmin University of China in the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=School_of_Liberal_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"School of Liberal Arts (page does not exist)\">School of Liberal Arts</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Liu_Xiaofeng_(academic)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">F\u00e4llman, Fredrik (2008). <i>Salvation and Modernity: Intellectuals and Faith in Contemporary China</i>. Lanham, MA: University Press of America. pp.&#160;21\u201339. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780761840909\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780761840909\">9780761840909</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Salvation+and+Modernity%3A+Intellectuals+and+Faith+in+Contemporary+China&amp;rft.place=Lanham%2C+MA&amp;rft.pages=21-39&amp;rft.pub=University+Press+of+America&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.isbn=9780761840909&amp;rft.aulast=F%C3%A4llman&amp;rft.aufirst=Fredrik&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALiu+Xiaofeng+%28academic%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">F\u00e4llman, <i>Salvation and Modernity</i>, 32.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Aikman, David (2003). <i>Jesus in Beijing: How Christianity is Transforming China and Changing the Global Balance of Power</i>. Washington, DC: Regnery Publishing, Inc. p.&#160;251. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-59698-025-9\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-59698-025-9\">978-1-59698-025-9</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Jesus+in+Beijing%3A+How+Christianity+is+Transforming+China+and+Changing+the+Global+Balance+of+Power&amp;rft.place=Washington%2C+DC&amp;rft.pages=251&amp;rft.pub=Regnery+Publishing%2C+Inc.&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-59698-025-9&amp;rft.aulast=Aikman&amp;rft.aufirst=David&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALiu+Xiaofeng+%28academic%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Marchal, Kai, (2017). <i>Carl Schmitt and Leo Strauss in the Chinese-speaking World: Reorienting the Political</i>. Lanham, Maryland: Lexington Books. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1498536264\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1498536264\">978-1498536264</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Carl+Schmitt+and+Leo+Strauss+in+the+Chinese-speaking+World%3A+Reorienting+the+Political&amp;rft.place=Lanham%2C+Maryland&amp;rft.pub=Lexington+Books&amp;rft.date=2017&amp;rft.isbn=978-1498536264&amp;rft.aulast=Marchal&amp;rft.aufirst=Kai%2C&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALiu+Xiaofeng+%28academic%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Christianity_in_China\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks collapsible collapsed navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"2\" style=\"-moz-box-shadow: inset 1px 1px 0 #EEE8AA, inset -1px -1px 0 #EEE8AA; -webkit-box-shadow: inset 1px 1px 0 #EEE8AA, inset -1px -1px 0 #EEE8AA; box-shadow: inset 1px 1px 0 #EEE8AA, inset -1px -1px 0 #EEE8AA;background:#FFFFF0;\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Christianity_and_China\" title=\"Template:Christianity and China\"><abbr title=\"View this template\" style=\"-moz-box-shadow: inset 1px 1px 0 #EEE8AA, inset -1px -1px 0 #EEE8AA; -webkit-box-shadow: inset 1px 1px 0 #EEE8AA, inset -1px -1px 0 #EEE8AA; box-shadow: inset 1px 1px 0 #EEE8AA, 